description: On March 23rd, the Egyptian Ministry of Health called on the Egyptians to stay at homes unless necessary to avoid the spread of the coronavirus (COVID-19) pandemic, after the number of infected people rose to 327 cases, including 14 deaths so far. The ministry sent SMSs to the citizens to avoid visits, gatherings, to wash hands constantly with soap and water, and to disinfect the surfaces of their furniture. It is necessary to avoid smoking as the virus poses risks to the smokers, the ministry said, asking the people to have healthy food. It is recommended that the elderly people and adults should exercise daily for 30 minutes, while the children should exercise for one hour, the statement said.

description:
As of 4th of June, The Egyptian Ministry of Health has abolished quarantine restrictions for Egyptians returning to their country on emergency flights via Cairo International Airport. The returnees will only be asked to sign a document saying that they will isolate themselves at home for one week until it is confirmed that they do not have coronavirus symptoms.

Previously everyone returning to Egypt on flights organized by the ministry of civil aviation had to stay in quarantine for 14 days, although this was reduced to seven days on 20 May.
type_sub_cat: Other Quarantine

description:
Egypt moved on Thursday to close all restaurants, cafes, cafeterias, casinos, nightclubs, bars, malls, shops and mobile food carts nationwide, from 7:00 pm until 6:00 am each day through March 31, as part of efforts to stop the spread of the coronavirus (COVID 19) outbreak.

Stores selling food stuffs such as bakeries, groceries, pharmacies and supermarkets, as well as delivery services, are exempted from the decree under Article two.
